article.description: — Elijah McCadden had a layup to tie the game and converted a pair of free throws with 17 seconds left to give Georgia Southern a 66-65 win over Louisiana-Lafayette on Saturday night.
article.headline: McCadden gets Georgia Southern past Louisiana, 66-65
article.linkText: McCadden gets Georgia Southern past Louisiana, 66-65
article.story: LAFAAYETTE, La. -- — Elijah McCadden had a layup to tie the game and converted a pair of free throws with 17 seconds left to give Georgia Southern a 66-65 win over Louisiana-Lafayette on Saturday night. McCadden came off the bench to score 21 points, converting 8 of 11 from the line and adding four assists, and Cam Bryant added 16 points and seven rebounds as the Eagles (10-9, 3-5 Horizon) got 45 of its 66 points from its bench. Kobe Julien led the Ragin' Cajuns (9-10, 4-5) with 19 points. Dou Gueye added 13 points and Jordan Brown chipped in 10 points off the bench. ------ https://www.espn.com/mens-college-basketball/boxscore/--/gameId/401371139 AP college basketball: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and https://twitter.com/AP--Top25
